{meta: title I Cared For You More Than I Knew}
{meta: artist Ernest Tubb}
{meta: writer Jimmie Rodgers}

{start_of_verse: Verse 1}
[C]You say it’s better if we drift [G7]apart
[C]Although you see that it’s breaking my heart
[G7]How can you leave me so lonely and blue
[C]Knowing just how I’ve been counting on you
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 2}
[G7]We once was so happy it all seems a shame
[C]And do you feel like that I am to blame
[G7]Dear if I failed you oh please tell me now
[C]And then maybe we can patch it up somehow
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 3}
[G7]Now that I’ve lost you the whole world seems wrong
[C]I don’t see how I can face it alone
[G7]For I’ve tried so hard to do right by you
[C]And really I cared for you more than I knew
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 4}
[G7]When I first met you I heard people say
[C]That there’d come a time when you’d treat me this way
[G7]I did not believe them I just let them rave
[C]Determined to stick by you clear to the grave
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 5}
[G7]It would have been better had we never met
[C]Then I would not have so much to forget
[G7]If I’d only dreamed dear that there’d come this day
[C]Five years I could have used better some way
{end_of_verse}

